<span id="freeTextContainer1751178294585255899">I know O&apos;Neill is considered one of the greatest, if not the greatest, American playwrights; and I LOVE Long Day&apos;s Journey into Night, however, I absolutely HATED this play. I had no &quot;in&quot; to the play. I didn&apos;t like any of the characters, therefore, I didn&apos;t care about any of them. Because of this I found it very difficult to read the long, drunken ramblings of each of the characters. I couldn&apos;t fathom any point to the play-If there was an over arching theme to it, I missed it, and don&apos;t care to </span>
  <span id="freeText1751178294585255899" style="display:none">I know O'Neill is considered one of the greatest, if not the greatest, American playwrights; and I LOVE Long Day's Journey into Night, however, I absolutely HATED this play. I had no "in" to the play. I didn't like any of the characters, therefore, I didn't care about any of them. Because of this I found it very difficult to read the long, drunken ramblings of each of the characters. I couldn't fathom any point to the play-If there was an over arching theme to it, I missed it, and don't care to find it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1751178294585255899" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

